#T_SP=custom.Span|label
#Text=*Description** Do you thrive on working on the cutting edge?
#Text=Working with innovators in the early stages of ideas and products?
#Text=Are you technologically savvy and forward-thinker?
#Text=Would you enjoy using your software development skills to deliver world-class applications?
#Text=Would you like to make an impact on the experience of millions of Humana members?
#Text=We are looking for a Sr.
#Text=Software Engineer, with experience in modern JavaScript, Node.js, React, Jest, and SQL/NoSQL data stores.
#Text=The team is organized around a product and is empowered to do the job.
#Text=We co-create with our end-users and follow human-centered design approach and agile development practices.
#Text=It's a distributed onshore/nearshore/offshore team that operates remotely, working Eastern Standard Time hours.
#Text=Our front-end web apps are written in React, and our back-end services are built using Java/Spring Boot.
#Text=We use a modern development process with continuous integration, continuous deployment, feature flags, automated... testing, and vulnerability scanning.
#Text=We ship in small increments, and we ship often.
#Text=Apps and services are deployed in Azure Cloud.
#Text=**Responsibilities** The Sr.
#Text=Software Engineer codes software applications based on business requirements.
#Text=The Sr.
#Text=Software Engineer work assignments are varied and frequently require interpretation and independent determination of the appropriate courses of action.
#Text=The Sr.
#Text=Software Engineer standardizes the quality assurance procedure for software.
#Text=Oversees testing and debugging and develops fixes.
#Text=Research and makes necessary adjustments and/or recommendations to resolve complex software related issues.
#Text=Understands department, segment, and organizational strategy and operating objectives, including their linkages to related areas.
#Text=Makes decisions regarding own work methods, occasionally in ambiguous situations, and requires minimal direction, mentors' junior engineers.
#Text=Follows established guidelines/procedures.

#Text=**Required Qualifications** + 5+ yrs of experience with frontend application development. + At least 3-5yrs of experience using a modern JavaScript framework, preferably React JS. + Good understanding of API's, Microservices Architecture, Testing Automation. + Must have knowledge of the branching & merging strategies, commits, and pull requests. + Must have experience performing code reviews and mentoring junior developers. + Proactive problem resolution, ability to work in a fast-paced multi-partner environment + Manage priorities, timelines, and deliverables, all-hands on deck contributor + Bachelor's degree in computer science or related field + Must be passionate about contributing to an organization focused on continuously improving consumer experiences. + Strong analytical and reasoning skills with an ability to visualize processes and outcomes.
#Text=Strategic thinker with strong analytic and problem-solving skills + Proficiency in troubleshooting software issues and debugging complex codebase.

#Text=Experience with performance profiling and optimization + Outstanding all-round communication skills and ability to work collaboratively **Preferred Qualifications** + Experience designing and building front-end and API solutions + Experience with cloud native solutions in public and hybrid cloud environment + Demonstrable experience with modern software development process, principles, and practices (continuous integration/continuous delivery, change management and version control, test-driven development, automated testing, peer-reviewed code) + Deep understanding of agile principles and how they can be flexibly applied + A passion for solving problems and providing workable solutions + Experience working on cross-functional/balanced product aligned teams + Experience with human-centered design approach + Healthcare business experience + Experience working with remote distributed teams + Master's Degree **Additional Information** Work-At-Home Requirements To ensure Home or Hybrid Home/Office associates' ability to work effectively, the self-provided internet service of Home or Hybrid Home/Office associates must meet the following criteria: + At minimum, a download speed of 25 Mbps and an upload speed of 10 Mbps is recommended; wireless, wired cable or DSL connection is suggested + Satellite, cellular and microwave connection can be used only if approved by leadership + Associates who live and work from Home in the state of California, Illinois, Montana, or South Dakota will be provided a bi-weekly payment for their internet expense. + Humana will provide Home or Hybrid Home/Office associates with telephone equipment appropriate to meet the business requirements for their position/job. + Work from a dedicated space lacking ongoing interruptions to protect member PHI / HIPAA information #LI-Remore This is a remote position **Scheduled Weekly Hours** 40Humana complies with all applicable federal civil rights laws and does not discriminate on the basis of race, color, national origin, age, disability, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity or religion.
#Text=We also provide free language interpreter services.
#Text=See our https://www.humana.com/legal/accessibility-resources?
